"faq": {
  "title": "FAQ",
  "subtitle": "Frequently Asked Questions",
  "newProductTitle": "How to import initial inventory for a new product?",
  "newProductContent": "You can use the 'New Inventory' button in the top right corner. In the dialog, select the warehouse, fill in SKU, product name, quantity, location, supplier, and other information, then click 'Submit'. For multiple records, you can also upload an Excel/CSV file through 'Batch Import', fill in the data according to the template format, and the system will automatically parse and complete the stock-in operation.",
  "outboundTitle": "How to perform outbound operations for existing inventory?",
  "outboundContent": "Find the corresponding SKU row in the inventory table, click the 'Outbound' button, fill in the outbound quantity, reason, and operator in the dialog. The system will automatically verify if the available stock is sufficient. If the outbound quantity is valid, click 'Confirm' to complete the outbound operation. The inventory quantity will be automatically deducted, and an outbound record will be generated in the 'Inventory Transactions'.",
  "transferTitle": "What is the process to transfer a product from Warehouse A to B?",
  "transferContent": "Transfer is a two-step process: First, click the 'Transfer' button on the product row in Warehouse A, select 'Source Warehouse' as A and 'Target Warehouse' as B, and enter the transfer quantity. The system will first perform a 'TRANSFER_OUT' operation from Warehouse A, then create a 'TRANSFER_IN' record in Warehouse B. After the transfer is complete, both inventories will be updated synchronously, and transaction details will be generated for each.",
  "transactionTitle": "How to view inventory transaction details for a specific SKU?",
  "transactionContent": "In the 'Actions' column of any inventory row in the table, click the 'View Transactions' button to navigate to the inventory transaction page for that SKU in that warehouse. The transaction page displays details of each inbound, outbound, transfer, and inventory adjustment operation in reverse chronological order, including operation time, quantity change, action type, operator, and remarks, making it easy to track historical records at any time."
},
